File: A person draped in a blanket during a cold front. Pixabay JOHANNESBURG - Wrap up warmly, Gauteng -- a cold front is here. The South African Weather Service confirms a serious drop in temperature this weekend. READ: Western Cape braces for cold fronts City of Johannesburg Emergency Management Services says it's on high alert to respond to any emergencies. It will focus in particular on 189 informal settlements. The service is urging people to keep an eye on paraffin stoves, heaters and candles, and not leave them unattended. ⚠️Media Release: Cold snap expected over parts of the country this weekend (20-23 May 2021). pic.twitter.com/JchB49uUbf